estimateProbit

Source: R/05-probitBoot.R
estimateProbit.Rd

estimateProbit

estimateProbit(x, w, statistic = bootPROBIT, params = "MUAC",
  outputColumns = "MUAC", replicates = 399)

Arguments

x

Indicators dataset produced by createOP with primary sampling unit (PSU) in column named PSU
w

A data frame with primary sampling unit (PSU) in column named psu and survey weight (i.e. PSU population) in column named pop
statistic

A function operating on data in x; fixed to bootPROBIT to perform probit estimation
params

Parameters (named columns in x) passed to the function specified in statistic; fixed to MUAC as indicator amenable to probit estimation
outputColumns

Names of columns in output data frame; fixed to MUAC
replicates

Number of bootstrap replicates

Value

Dataframe of boot estimates using bootPROBIT function

Examples

  #
  test <- estimateClassic(x = indicators.ALL,
                          w = testPSU,
                          replicates = 9)
